{"title":"Mosaic Cycles: GT-1 i45 and New Artist Series Finish Scale","link":"https://theradavist.com/mosaic-cycles-gt-1-i45-scale-finish/","date":1710253033000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"3500\" height=\"2334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Mosaic_Cycles_Scale_03.jpg?fit=1200,2334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Mosaic_Cycles_Scale_03.jpg?w=3500&amp;quality=75 3500w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Mosaic_Cycles_Scale_03.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Mosaic_Cycles_Scale_03.jpg?resize=2000,1334&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Mosaic_Cycles_Scale_03.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Mosaic_Cycles_Scale_03.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Mosaic_Cycles_Scale_03.jpg?resize=2048,1366&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>Making its debut alongside the new <a href=\"https://www.mosaiccycles.com/gt-1-i45\" target=\"_blank\">GT-1 i45</a>, another integrated version of a Mosaic gravel model is Artist Series <a href=\"https://www.mosaiccycles.com/artistseries\" target=\"_blank\">No.6 – Scale</a>. Designed, prototyped, and painted by Mosaic founder Aaron Barcheck, Scale is a creative and unique spin on the Mosaic Knockout layout using a randomized, stamped paint technique.<span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"3500\" height=\"2334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Mosaic_Cycles_Scale_01.jpg?fit=1200,2334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Mosaic_Cycles_Scale_01.jpg?w=3500&amp;quality=75 3500w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Mosaic_Cycles_Scale_01.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Mosaic_Cycles_Scale_01.jpg?resize=2000,1334&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Mosaic_Cycles_Scale_01.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Mosaic_Cycles_Scale_01.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Mosaic_Cycles_Scale_01.jpg?resize=2048,1366&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p><span>This results in a reptilian-like (of fish if you don’t like snakes and lizards) finish on the frames. Each Scale paint job will be unique due to the random nature of the pattern and is available in a number of colors.</span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"3500\" height=\"2334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Mosaic_Cycles_Scale_02.jpg?fit=1200,2334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Mosaic_Cycles_Scale_02.jpg?w=3500&amp;quality=75 3500w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Mosaic_Cycles_Scale_02.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Mosaic_Cycles_Scale_02.jpg?resize=2000,1334&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Mosaic_Cycles_Scale_02.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Mosaic_Cycles_Scale_02.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Mosaic_Cycles_Scale_02.jpg?resize=2048,1366&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p><span>Scale is available now in 6 stunning colorways, each as unique as the individuals they’re made for. Scale marks the sixth edition to the Mosaic Artist Series which was first introduced in 2019 and has been updated annually on a limited-edition basis.</span></p>\n<p>See the new <a href=\"https://www.mosaiccycles.com/gt-1-i45\" target=\"_blank\">GT-1 i45</a> and <a href=\"https://www.mosaiccycles.com/artistseries\" target=\"_blank\">Scale</a> at <a href=\"https://www.mosaiccycles.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Mosaic Cycles</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/mosaic-cycles-gt-1-i45-scale-finish/\">Mosaic Cycles: GT-1 i45 and New Artist Series Finish Scale</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"cb142b131d595d0d84ef49d4586caa0b033998fab0ccda5eff8bac5d06ae726d","category":"Cycling"}